<p>It is not economical to spend a lot of resources to design a brand identity that doesn’t carry a lot of intrinsic value or longevity. But you need a brand to start a company. At the minimum, you need a logo for the pitch deck, business cards, landing pages, and Email signature.</p>
<p>In other words, startups need brand identity quickly but for cheap. Those are the two lines in the quality triangle: time and cost. To maintain quality, startup founders need to cut down the scope. Where to cut in the scope?</p>
